"{\"uid\": \"smh.com.au-world-europe-french-police-arrest-alleged-russian-spy-over-plot-to-destabilise-olympics-20240725-p5jwco.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are sorry, this feature is currently unavailable.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are working to restore it.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please try again later.\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was published1yearago  Add articles to your saved list and come back to them any time.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris:An alleged Russian spy who spent time as a contestant on TV cooking shows has been arrested in France on suspicion of plotting to \\\"destabilise\\\" the country just days before the Olympic Games opening ceremony in Paris.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 201, \"end\": 206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999868578, \"rank\": 1.3132492765931612e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 218, \"end\": 225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.7533855243878032, \"rank\": 0.2295891848061218, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9983070800340689, \"rank\": 0.0009373150178806044, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 418, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999868578, \"rank\": 1.3132492765931612e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 40-year-old man was detained on Tuesday after police raided his house at the request of French intelligence agencies, the prosecutor's office said in a statement.\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 518, \"end\": 546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French intelligence agencies\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was reported they had been following him for several months.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French police raided the man's house.Credit:Thomas Padilla  The man is now being investigated over sharing intelligence with a foreign power in an attempt to \\\"provoke hostilities in France\\\" and has been placed in pre-trial detention.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1765798648794033e-40, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 702, \"end\": 708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.997555732036559, \"rank\": 0.0023893558288816934, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 709, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vicente_Padilla\", \"score\": 0.9999990883383879, \"rank\": 9.11659882239941e-07, \"text\": \"Padilla\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vicente_Padilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vicente_Padilla\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9983070800340689, \"rank\": 0.0009373150178806044, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The offence carries a maximum sentence of 30 years in prison.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French media quoted sources close to the inquiry as saying the man had been involved in a \\\"large-scale\\\" pro-Russian operation, believed to be linked with Moscow's special forces, which are a part of the security agency FSB.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 955, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9774208435358454, \"rank\": 0.01677664221619883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 9.755824072328971e-13, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Security_Service\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2120903459258155e-40, \"text\": \"FSB\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Security_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Security_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Le Mondesaid a document indicating that he was a member of an elite unit of the security agency that succeeded the KGB was found at his home.\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KGB\", \"score\": 0.9999978391211398, \"rank\": 2.160883354421386e-06, \"text\": \"KGB\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KGB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KGB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The newspaper suggested that French counterespionage operatives had been following him since at least May when he was banned from boarding a flight from Turkey to France because he was drunk.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9774208435358454, \"rank\": 0.01677664221619883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1476, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9999999203573712, \"rank\": 7.964280221594773e-08, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 1486, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9983070800340689, \"rank\": 0.0009373150178806044, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having rerouted through Bulgaria, he called an FSB handler and said: \\\"The French are going to have an opening ceremony like there has never been,\\\" according toLe Monde.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"score\": 0.9983275696108416, \"rank\": 0.001301049447423588, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\"}, {\"begin\": 1562, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Security_Service\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2120903459258155e-40, \"text\": \"FSB\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Security_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Security_Service\"}, {\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9774208435358454, \"rank\": 0.01677664221619883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The man was reported to have first arrived in France in 2010 where he attended a Parisian cooking school and then worked in a luxury hotel in Courchevel, the Alpine ski resort.\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1731, \"end\": 1737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9983070800340689, \"rank\": 0.0009373150178806044, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courchevel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6257780577779542e-20, \"text\": \"Courchevel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courchevel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courchevel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He now describes himself as a private chef, posts cooking tutorials on social media and has featured in Russian television cooking shows, the report added.\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia's embassy in Paris said it had not received official notification of the detention and had \\\"proactively asked them for clarification\\\".\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999995216058, \"rank\": 4.734259687055736e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2039, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999868578, \"rank\": 1.3132492765931612e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics officials said on Sunday they feared the Games would be further targeted by misinformation and cyberattacks over the next three weeks following recent incidents which have been widely blamed on Russia.\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2365, \"end\": 2371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999995216058, \"rank\": 4.734259687055736e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"IOC spokesman Mark Adams said it was clear that a targeted campaign was already under way following a handful of incidents including a feature-length fake documentary that emerged in 2023 titledOlympics has Fallen,which used AI-generated audio to impersonate Hollywood star Tom Cruise.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2374, \"end\": 2377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.70997594475091e-17, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2388, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333321225, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}, {\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998781277, \"rank\": 1.2159318935441537e-10, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2648, \"end\": 2658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A report published in June from the Microsoft Threat Analysis Centre said Russia was seeking to undermine the Olympics by ramping up malign disinformation campaigns against France, French President Emmanuel Macron and the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"score\": 0.9999911276820749, \"rank\": 8.871761912313494e-06, \"text\": \"Microsoft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\"}, {\"begin\": 2735, \"end\": 2741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999995216058, \"rank\": 4.734259687055736e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2834, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9983070800340689, \"rank\": 0.0009373150178806044, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The campaign has involved the creation of fake websites replicating authentic French media outlets to fuel concern about violence and terrorism at the Games.\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2995, \"end\": 3001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9774208435358454, \"rank\": 0.01677664221619883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Microsoft said there had also been fake press releases designed to trick internet users into thinking they were issued by the CIA, warning fans to stay away from the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"score\": 0.9999911276820749, \"rank\": 8.871761912313494e-06, \"text\": \"Microsoft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\"}, {\"begin\": 3202, \"end\": 3205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Intelligence_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.31786729628843e-17, \"text\": \"CIA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Intelligence_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Intelligence_Agency\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"with agencies  Get a note directly from our foreign correspondents on what's making headlines around the world.Sign up for the weekly What in the World newsletter here.\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a92025\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3438, \"entities\": []}]}"